"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-08-08-olympic-final-descends-brawl-dutch-star-celebrates-opponents-face-21390380\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"The final of the men'sOlympichockey descended into a scuffle after Dutch player Duco Telgenkamp celebrated the winning goal by 'shushing' in the face of theGermangoalkeeper.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 173, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 80, \"end\": 84, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duco\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Duco\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duco\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duco\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Following a 1-1 draw in regulation time, the gold medal match inParisheaded to a shootout to decide the winner.\", \"from\": 175, \"to\": 286, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After a series of saves from Dutch keeper Pirmin Blaak, it was Telgenkamp who fired past German keeper Jean-Paul Danneberg to hand the Netherlands their first men's gold medal since 2000.\", \"from\": 288, \"to\": 475, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 330, \"end\": 342, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pirmin_Blaak\", \"score\": 0.9999999745145945, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pirmin Blaak\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pirmin_Blaak\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pirmin_Blaak\"}, {\"begin\": 377, \"end\": 383, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"score\": 0.7191717604439624, \"rank\": 0.36872262712930604, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\"}, {\"begin\": 423, \"end\": 434, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_men's_national_field_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.8223637784551197, \"rank\": 0.21591641913390947, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_men's_national_field_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_men's_national_field_hockey_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, the post-match celebrations quickly took an ugly turn as Telgenkamp rushed towards Danneberg and performed a 'shushing' gesture directly in his opponent's face.\", \"from\": 477, \"to\": 646, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"German player Niklas Wellen, in particular, took issue with the gesture and furiously raced to confront Telgenkamp while other Dutch players celebrated around them.\", \"from\": 648, \"to\": 812, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 648, \"end\": 654, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"score\": 0.7191717604439624, \"rank\": 0.36872262712930604, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\"}, {\"begin\": 662, \"end\": 675, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Niklas_Wellen\", \"score\": 0.9999997747816249, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Niklas Wellen\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Niklas_Wellen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Niklas_Wellen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dutch player Floris Middendorp\\u00a0moved to prevent Wellen from reaching Telgenkamp, with the latter continuing to taunt his opposition by sticking his tongue out.\", \"from\": 814, \"to\": 973, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And as a scuffle broke out between both sides, officials were eventually forced to step in to curtail the pushing and shoving.\", \"from\": 975, \"to\": 1101, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the aftermath of the incident, Telgenkamp apologised for his celebration, which was brought on by Danneberg's pre-match comments, in which he claimed the Dutch were afraid of his German side.\", \"from\": 1103, \"to\": 1297, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1285, \"end\": 1291, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"score\": 0.7191717604439624, \"rank\": 0.36872262712930604, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'In hindsight, I should not have gone to him.\", \"from\": 1299, \"to\": 1344, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I regret that.\", \"from\": 1345, \"to\": 1359, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I also apologise,' he said.\", \"from\": 1360, \"to\": 1387, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'I should have let it go and it wasn't very smart.\", \"from\": 1388, \"to\": 1438, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Things got out of hand after Netherlands won hockey gold \\u00f0\\u009f\\u0098\\u00ac#BBCOlympics#Paris2024#Olympicspic.twitter.com/YOa0NkrpfE  'But it's also a bit the nature of the beast.\", \"from\": 1440, \"to\": 1605, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1469, \"end\": 1480, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_men's_national_field_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.8223637784551197, \"rank\": 0.21591641913390947, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_men's_national_field_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_men's_national_field_hockey_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I can be very cool-headed, but I can also let myself go.\", \"from\": 1606, \"to\": 1662, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Is that part of it?\", \"from\": 1663, \"to\": 1682, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'He affected me personally.\", \"from\": 1684, \"to\": 1711, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sports are not business, it does not take much to be provoked.\", \"from\": 1712, \"to\": 1774, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That's how I go into the match.\", \"from\": 1775, \"to\": 1806, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I felt a bit offended.'\", \"from\": 1807, \"to\": 1830, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"German forward Christopher Ruhr, meanwhile, suggested his team deserved to win the match and labelled the Dutch 'lucky' in walking away with the gold medal.\", \"from\": 1832, \"to\": 1988, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1832, \"end\": 1838, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"score\": 0.7191717604439624, \"rank\": 0.36872262712930604, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1859, \"end\": 1863, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ruhr\", \"score\": 0.999610563123464, \"rank\": 0.0003814132204838065, \"text\": \"Ruhr\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ruhr\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ruhr\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'We deserved to win the gold medal.\", \"from\": 1990, \"to\": 2025, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was an incredibly close match that came down to the shoot-out,' Ruhr said.\", \"from\": 2026, \"to\": 2103, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2093, \"end\": 2097, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ruhr\", \"score\": 0.999610563123464, \"rank\": 0.0003814132204838065, \"text\": \"Ruhr\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ruhr\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ruhr\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'The Dutch team had the luck today, but our overall performance was strong.\", \"from\": 2105, \"to\": 2180, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I think it is phenomenal that we made it to two finals at major sports events and won major knockout games.'\", \"from\": 2181, \"to\": 2289, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For more stories like this,check our sport page.\", \"from\": 2291, \"to\": 2339, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow Metro Sport for the latest news onFacebook,TwitterandInstagram.\", \"from\": 2341, \"to\": 2411, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ArrowMORE:Noah Lyles hits back after USA sprinter is slammed for running Olympic final with Covid  ArrowMORE:New footage shows Travis Scott dragged away by cops after drunke